          <h2 class="h2-title">
            Beyond the Courtroom: The Strategic Advantage of Alternative Dispute
            Resolution (ADR) in Nigeria
          </h2>
          <div class="blog-detail-text-box">
            <p>
              For decades, the default path for resolving commercial disputes in
              Nigeria has been through traditional litigation. While the courts
              remain a fundamental pillar of our justice system, the realities
              of today's fast-paced business environment—demanding speed,
              confidentiality, and commercial pragmatism—have elevated the
              importance of Alternative Dispute Resolution (ADR).
            </p>
            <p>
              ADR refers to a range of processes, including arbitration,
              mediation, and conciliation, that allow parties to resolve
              disputes outside of the courtroom. For businesses operating in
              Nigeria, embracing ADR is no longer just an 'alternative'; it is a
              strategic decision that can protect assets, preserve
              relationships, and deliver efficient, commercially sensible
              outcomes. The enactment of the Arbitration and Mediation Act,
              2023, has further modernized the framework, making Nigeria an even
              more attractive seat for arbitration.
            </p>
          </div>
