              At O. A. Omonuwa SAN & Co., we guide our clients in selecting the
              most appropriate resolution mechanism. Arbitration offers a
              private, binding, and often expert-led process, ideal for complex
              technical or commercial disagreements. Mediation, on the other
              hand, provides a structured negotiation facilitated by a neutral
              third party, empowering the disputants to craft their own
              solutions. This is particularly valuable where the continuation of
              a commercial relationship is a priority. Understanding the nuances
              of each ADR method is critical to leveraging their full strategic
              potential.
            </p>
